19bool IsStencilNoOp(GLenum stencilFunc,
20 GLenum stencilFail,
21 GLenum stencilPassDepthFail,
22 GLenum stencilPassDepthPass)
23{
24 const bool isNeverAndKeep = stencilFunc == GL_NEVER && stencilFail == GL_KEEP;
25 const bool isAlwaysAndKeepOrAllKeep = (stencilFunc == GL_ALWAYS || stencilFail == GL_KEEP) &&
26 stencilPassDepthFail == GL_KEEP &&
27 stencilPassDepthPass == GL_KEEP;
28
29 return isNeverAndKeep || isAlwaysAndKeepOrAllKeep;
30}
31
32// Calculate whether the range [outsideLow, outsideHigh] encloses the range [insideLow, insideHigh]
33bool EnclosesRange(int outsideLow, int outsideHigh, int insideLow, int insideHigh)
34{
35 return outsideLow <= insideLow && outsideHigh >= insideHigh;
36}

39RasterizerState::RasterizerState()
40{
41 memset(this, 0, sizeof(RasterizerState));
42
43 rasterizerDiscard = false;
44 cullFace = false;
45 cullMode = CullFaceMode::Back;
46 frontFace = GL_CCW;
47 polygonOffsetFill = false;
48 polygonOffsetFactor = 0.0f;
49 polygonOffsetUnits = 0.0f;
50 pointDrawMode = false;
51 multiSample = false;
52 dither = true;
53}

102DepthStencilState::DepthStencilState()
103{
104 memset(this, 0, sizeof(DepthStencilState));
105
106 depthTest = false;
107 depthFunc = GL_LESS;
108 depthMask = true;
109 stencilTest = false;
110 stencilFunc = GL_ALWAYS;
111 stencilMask = static_cast<GLuint>(-1);
112 stencilWritemask = static_cast<GLuint>(-1);
113 stencilBackFunc = GL_ALWAYS;
114 stencilBackMask = static_cast<GLuint>(-1);
115 stencilBackWritemask = static_cast<GLuint>(-1);
116 stencilFail = GL_KEEP;
117 stencilPassDepthFail = GL_KEEP;
118 stencilPassDepthPass = GL_KEEP;
119 stencilBackFail = GL_KEEP;
120 stencilBackPassDepthFail = GL_KEEP;
121 stencilBackPassDepthPass = GL_KEEP;
122}
123
124DepthStencilState::DepthStencilState(const DepthStencilState &other)
125{
126 memcpy(this, &other, sizeof(DepthStencilState));
127}
128
129bool DepthStencilState::isDepthMaskedOut() const
130{
131 return !depthMask;
132}
133
134bool DepthStencilState::isStencilMaskedOut() const
135{
136 return (stencilMask & stencilWritemask) == 0;
137}
138
139bool DepthStencilState::isStencilNoOp() const
140{
141 return isStencilMaskedOut() ||
142 IsStencilNoOp(stencilFunc, stencilFail, stencilPassDepthFail, stencilPassDepthPass);
143}
144
145bool DepthStencilState::isStencilBackNoOp() const
146{
147 const bool isStencilBackMaskedOut = (stencilBackMask & stencilBackWritemask) == 0;
148 return isStencilBackMaskedOut ||
149 IsStencilNoOp(stencilBackFunc, stencilBackFail, stencilBackPassDepthFail,
150 stencilBackPassDepthPass);
151}
152
153bool operator==(const DepthStencilState &a, const DepthStencilState &b)
154{
155 return memcmp(&a, &b, sizeof(DepthStencilState)) == 0;
156}
157
158bool operator!=(const DepthStencilState &a, const DepthStencilState &b)
159{
160 return !(a == b);
161}

163SamplerState::SamplerState()
164{
165 memset(this, 0, sizeof(SamplerState));
166
167 setMinFilter(GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR);
168 setMagFilter(GL_LINEAR);
169 setWrapS(GL_REPEAT);
170 setWrapT(GL_REPEAT);
171 setWrapR(GL_REPEAT);
172 setMaxAnisotropy(1.0f);
173 setMinLod(-1000.0f);
174 setMaxLod(1000.0f);
175 setCompareMode(GL_NONE);
176 setCompareFunc(GL_LEQUAL);
177 setSRGBDecode(GL_DECODE_EXT);
178}

184// static
185SamplerState SamplerState::CreateDefaultForTarget(TextureType type)
186{
187 SamplerState state;
188
189 // According to OES_EGL_image_external and ARB_texture_rectangle: For external textures, the
190 // default min filter is GL_LINEAR and the default s and t wrap modes are GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE.
191 if (type == TextureType::External || type == TextureType::Rectangle)
192 {
193 state.mMinFilter = GL_LINEAR;
194 state.mWrapS = GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE;
195 state.mWrapT = GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE;
196 }
197
198 return state;
199}

266void SamplerState::updateWrapTCompareMode()
267{
268 uint8_t wrap = static_cast<uint8_t>(FromGLenum<WrapMode>(mWrapT));
269 uint8_t compare = static_cast<uint8_t>(mCompareMode == GL_NONE ? 0x10 : 0x00);
270 mCompleteness.typed.wrapTCompareMode = wrap | compare;
271}

281BlendStateExt::BlendStateExt(const size_t drawBuffers)
282 : mMaxFactorMask(FactorStorage::GetMask(drawBuffers)),
283 mSrcColor(FactorStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendFactorType::One, mMaxFactorMask)),
284 mDstColor(FactorStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendFactorType::Zero, mMaxFactorMask)),
285 mSrcAlpha(FactorStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendFactorType::One, mMaxFactorMask)),
286 mDstAlpha(FactorStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendFactorType::Zero, mMaxFactorMask)),
287 mMaxEquationMask(EquationStorage::GetMask(drawBuffers)),
288 mEquationColor(EquationStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendEquationType::Add, mMaxEquationMask)),
289 mEquationAlpha(EquationStorage::GetReplicatedValue(BlendEquationType::Add, mMaxEquationMask)),
290 mMaxColorMask(ColorMaskStorage::GetMask(drawBuffers)),
291 mColorMask(ColorMaskStorage::GetReplicatedValue(PackColorMask(true, true, true, true),
292 mMaxColorMask)),
293 mMaxEnabledMask(0xFF >> (8 - drawBuffers)),
294 mEnabledMask(),
295 mMaxDrawBuffers(drawBuffers)
296{}

554
555static void MinMax(int a, int b, int *minimum, int *maximum)
556{
557 if (a < b)
558 {
559 *minimum = a;
560 *maximum = b;
561 }
562 else
563 {
564 *minimum = b;
565 *maximum = a;
566 }
567}
568
569Rectangle Rectangle::flip(bool flipX, bool flipY) const
570{
571 Rectangle flipped = *this;
572 if (flipX)
573 {
574 flipped.x = flipped.x + flipped.width;
575 flipped.width = -flipped.width;
576 }
577 if (flipY)
578 {
579 flipped.y = flipped.y + flipped.height;
580 flipped.height = -flipped.height;
581 }
582 return flipped;
583}
584
585Rectangle Rectangle::removeReversal() const
586{
587 return flip(isReversedX(), isReversedY());
588}
589
590bool Rectangle::encloses(const gl::Rectangle &inside) const
591{
592 return x0() <= inside.x0() && y0() <= inside.y0() && x1() >= inside.x1() && y1() >= inside.y1();
593}
594
595bool ClipRectangle(const Rectangle &source, const Rectangle &clip, Rectangle *intersection)
596{
597 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> sourceX2(source.x);
598 sourceX2 += source.width;
599 if (!sourceX2.IsValid())
600 {
601 return false;
602 }
603 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> sourceY2(source.y);
604 sourceY2 += source.height;
605 if (!sourceY2.IsValid())
606 {
607 return false;
608 }
609
610 int minSourceX, maxSourceX, minSourceY, maxSourceY;
611 MinMax(source.x, sourceX2.ValueOrDie(), &minSourceX, &maxSourceX);
612 MinMax(source.y, sourceY2.ValueOrDie(), &minSourceY, &maxSourceY);
613
614 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> clipX2(clip.x);
615 clipX2 += clip.width;
616 if (!clipX2.IsValid())
617 {
618 return false;
619 }
620 angle::CheckedNumeric<int> clipY2(clip.y);
621 clipY2 += clip.height;
622 if (!clipY2.IsValid())
623 {
624 return false;
625 }
626
627 int minClipX, maxClipX, minClipY, maxClipY;
628 MinMax(clip.x, clipX2.ValueOrDie(), &minClipX, &maxClipX);
629 MinMax(clip.y, clipY2.ValueOrDie(), &minClipY, &maxClipY);
630
631 if (minSourceX >= maxClipX || maxSourceX <= minClipX || minSourceY >= maxClipY ||
632 maxSourceY <= minClipY)
633 {
634 return false;
635 }
636
637 int x = std::max(minSourceX, minClipX);
638 int y = std::max(minSourceY, minClipY);
639 int width = std::min(maxSourceX, maxClipX) - x;
640 int height = std::min(maxSourceY, maxClipY) - y;
641
642 if (intersection)
643 {
644 intersection->x = x;
645 intersection->y = y;
646 intersection->width = width;
647 intersection->height = height;
648 }
649 return width != 0 && height != 0;
650}
651
652void GetEnclosingRectangle(const Rectangle &rect1, const Rectangle &rect2, Rectangle *rectUnion)
653{
654 // All callers use non-flipped framebuffer-size-clipped rectangles, so both flip and overflow
655 // are impossible.
656 ASSERT(!rect1.isReversedX() && !rect1.isReversedY());
657 ASSERT(!rect2.isReversedX() && !rect2.isReversedY());
658 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(rect1.x) + rect1.width).IsValid());
659 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(rect1.y) + rect1.height).IsValid());
660 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(rect2.x) + rect2.width).IsValid());
661 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(rect2.y) + rect2.height).IsValid());
662
663 // This function calculates a rectangle that covers both input rectangles:
664 //
665 // +---------+
666 // rect1 --> | |
667 // | +---+-----+
668 // | | | | <-- rect2
669 // +-----+---+ |
670 // | |
671 // +---------+
672 //
673 // xy0 = min(rect1.xy0, rect2.xy0)
674 // \
675 // +---------+-----+
676 // union --> | . |
677 // | + . + . . +
678 // | . . |
679 // + . . + . + |
680 // | . |
681 // +-----+---------+
682 // /
683 // xy1 = max(rect1.xy1, rect2.xy1)
684
685 int x0 = std::min(rect1.x0(), rect2.x0());
686 int y0 = std::min(rect1.y0(), rect2.y0());
687
688 int x1 = std::max(rect1.x1(), rect2.x1());
689 int y1 = std::max(rect1.y1(), rect2.y1());
690
691 rectUnion->x = x0;
692 rectUnion->y = y0;
693 rectUnion->width = x1 - x0;
694 rectUnion->height = y1 - y0;
695}
696
697void ExtendRectangle(const Rectangle &source, const Rectangle &extend, Rectangle *extended)
698{
699 // All callers use non-flipped framebuffer-size-clipped rectangles, so both flip and overflow
700 // are impossible.
701 ASSERT(!source.isReversedX() && !source.isReversedY());
702 ASSERT(!extend.isReversedX() && !extend.isReversedY());
703 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(source.x) + source.width).IsValid());
704 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(source.y) + source.height).IsValid());
705 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(extend.x) + extend.width).IsValid());
706 ASSERT((angle::CheckedNumeric<int>(extend.y) + extend.height).IsValid());
707
708 int x0 = source.x0();
709 int x1 = source.x1();
710 int y0 = source.y0();
711 int y1 = source.y1();
712
713 const int extendX0 = extend.x0();
714 const int extendX1 = extend.x1();
715 const int extendY0 = extend.y0();
716 const int extendY1 = extend.y1();
717
718 // For each side of the rectangle, calculate whether it can be extended by the second rectangle.
719 // If so, extend it and continue for the next side with the new dimensions.
720
721 // Left: Reduce x0 if the second rectangle's vertical edge covers the source's:
722 //
723 // +--- - - - +--- - - -
724 // | |
725 // | +--------------+ +-----------------+
726 // | | source | --> | source |
727 // | +--------------+ +-----------------+
728 // | |
729 // +--- - - - +--- - - -
730 //
731 const bool enclosesHeight = EnclosesRange(extendY0, extendY1, y0, y1);
732 if (extendX0 < x0 && extendX1 >= x0 && enclosesHeight)
733 {
734 x0 = extendX0;
735 }
736
737 // Right: Increase x1 simiarly.
738 if (extendX0 <= x1 && extendX1 > x1 && enclosesHeight)
739 {
740 x1 = extendX1;
741 }
742
743 // Top: Reduce y0 if the second rectangle's horizontal edge covers the source's potentially
744 // extended edge.
745 const bool enclosesWidth = EnclosesRange(extendX0, extendX1, x0, x1);
746 if (extendY0 < y0 && extendY1 >= y0 && enclosesWidth)
747 {
748 y0 = extendY0;
749 }
750
751 // Right: Increase y1 simiarly.
752 if (extendY0 <= y1 && extendY1 > y1 && enclosesWidth)
753 {
754 y1 = extendY1;
755 }
756
757 extended->x = x0;
758 extended->y = y0;
759 extended->width = x1 - x0;
760 extended->height = y1 - y0;
761}
762
763bool Box::operator==(const Box &other) const
764{
765 return (x == other.x && y == other.y && z == other.z && width == other.width &&
766 height == other.height && depth == other.depth);
767}
768
769bool Box::operator!=(const Box &other) const
770{
771 return !(*this == other);
772}
773
774Rectangle Box::toRect() const
775{
776 ASSERT(z == 0 && depth == 1);
777 return Rectangle(x, y, width, height);
778}

780bool Box::coversSameExtent(const Extents &size) const
781{
782 return x == 0 && y == 0 && z == 0 && width == size.width && height == size.height &&
783 depth == size.depth;
784}

806bool ValidateComponentTypeMasks(unsigned long outputTypes,
807 unsigned long inputTypes,
808 unsigned long outputMask,
809 unsigned long inputMask)
810{
811 static_assert(IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS <= kMaxComponentTypeMaskIndex,
812 "Output/input masks should fit into 16 bits - 1 bit per draw buffer. The "
813 "corresponding type masks should fit into 32 bits - 2 bits per draw buffer.");
814 static_assert(MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS <= kMaxComponentTypeMaskIndex,
815 "Output/input masks should fit into 16 bits - 1 bit per attrib. The "
816 "corresponding type masks should fit into 32 bits - 2 bits per attrib.");
817
818 // For performance reasons, draw buffer and attribute type validation is done using bit masks.
819 // We store two bits representing the type split, with the low bit in the lower 16 bits of the
820 // variable, and the high bit in the upper 16 bits of the variable. This is done so we can AND
821 // with the elswewhere used DrawBufferMask or AttributeMask.
822
823 // OR the masks with themselves, shifted 16 bits. This is to match our split type bits.
824 outputMask |= (outputMask << kMaxComponentTypeMaskIndex);
825 inputMask |= (inputMask << kMaxComponentTypeMaskIndex);
826
827 // To validate:
828 // 1. Remove any indexes that are not enabled in the input (& inputMask)
829 // 2. Remove any indexes that exist in output, but not in input (& outputMask)
830 // 3. Use == to verify equality
831 return (outputTypes & inputMask) == ((inputTypes & outputMask) & inputMask);
832}
833
834GLsizeiptr GetBoundBufferAvailableSize(const OffsetBindingPointer<Buffer> &binding)
835{
836 Buffer *buffer = binding.get();
837 if (buffer)
838 {
839 if (binding.getSize() == 0)
840 return static_cast<GLsizeiptr>(buffer->getSize());
841 angle::CheckedNumeric<GLintptr> offset = binding.getOffset();
842 angle::CheckedNumeric<GLsizeiptr> size = binding.getSize();
843 angle::CheckedNumeric<GLsizeiptr> bufferSize = buffer->getSize();
844 auto end = offset + size;
845 auto clampedSize = size;
846 auto difference = end - bufferSize;
847 if (!difference.IsValid())
848 {
849 return 0;
850 }
851 if (difference.ValueOrDie() > 0)
852 {
853 clampedSize = size - difference;
854 }
855 return clampedSize.ValueOrDefault(0);
856 }
857 else
858 {
859 return 0;
860 }
861}
